            , a <rs id="t18310908-216-viclabel1118" type="occupation">hosier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-216-victim1613 t18310908-216-viclabel1118"></join>, in <placeName id="t18310908-216-crimeloc1119">the Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-216-crimeloc1119" type="placeName" value="the Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-216-crimeloc1119" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-216-off1116 t18310908-216-crimeloc1119"></join>. On the 14th of July, about half-past three o'clock, I found the glass of the window broken and thirteen handkerchiefs taken out; I looked round, and the Policeman brought the two prisoners back to the shop - he had some of the handkerchiefs in his hand; I had not seen the prisoners at the window.</p>
               <p>JOSEPH MORTON. I am a Policeman. I was on duty, and saw the prisoners standing at Mr. Brown's shop window for about one minute; they then both ran away together; I followed, and took them; Wright took two handkerchiefs out of his bosom, and said, "I found these two, and will give them you - they are not mine;" Jones had nothing; on the way to the watch-house he abused me most scandalously, and struck me twice in the face; I did not see Wright drop any thing, but a gentleman picked up these six handkerchiefs in the Strand, and gave them to me, as I took them to the station-house; Jones got from me, but was secured again.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-216-person1616">
                  WILLIAM 
                  TREWATHER
               <interp inst="t18310908-216-person1616" type="surname" value="TREWATHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-216-person1616" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-216-person1616" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I searched Wright after he was taken, and found five handkerchiefs, between his shirt and skin.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Wright's Defence. I saw something in the window, and thought it was a bill; I looked at it, and a young man who stood there threw the handkerchiefs down - I picked them up, and gave them to the Policeman.</p>
               <p>Jones' Defence. I do not know this boy, and was not with him.</p>
               <p>WRIGHT - <rs id="t18310908-216-verdict1120" type="verdictDescription">
